Put the salt and water into a large saucepan, dissolve over a low heat and then leave the brine to cool.Put the prepared shallots into the brine, weight down with a plate and leave in a cool place for 24 hours.The next day put the vinegar and all the spices and sugar into a saucepan, bring to the boil and leave to infuse and cool.Drain the shallots and carefully pack into the jars. Pour over the infused vinegar and the spices. Cover the jars with a screw top lid and leave in a cool dark place for 3-4 weeks before eating.